modules.description: This module renders and validates Google reCAPTCHA V2 challenges with support for theme and size customization. It works with string identifiers, theme variants (Light, Dark), and data size variants (Compact, Normal). Concrete use cases include embedding reCAPTCHA widgets in web forms and verifying user responses server-side using a secret key.

Performs server-side validation of reCAPTCHA v3 tokens using a secret key. Accepts a token, an optional expected action string, and a callback to handle the response. Used to verify user interactions with forms or APIs by assessing the token's score and matching action.

This module handles client-side rendering and server-side validation of Google reCAPTCHA challenges. It works with reCAPTCHA tokens, secret keys, and configuration options like theme and size. Use it to embed reCAPTCHA widgets in web forms and verify user responses by checking token validity and action match in server-side logic.
